# Reference for the gitignored profile environment files written by
# Setup-Runner.ps1. The default profile uses `.env`; named profiles use
# `.env.<profile>`. Never commit either form because it holds your PAT.

# Written by Setup-Runner.ps1. Token = your -Token PAT, else your gh CLI token
# (gh auth token). The pool uses it ONLY to register/remove runners. Needs
# Administration: Read and write on each repo.
ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Runner scope: repo (default) | org | ent. Repository targets and mutable worker
# counts live in `.pitcrew-state/<profile>/desired-capacity.json`, not this
# secret-bearing environment file.
RUNNER_SCOPE=repo
# ORG_NAME=
# ENTERPRISE_NAME=

# Direct Compose and pre-reconciliation environments can bootstrap desired state
# once when neither desired nor last-valid state exists. Setup-generated files do
# not include these values; use Setup-Runner.ps1 for subsequent capacity changes.
# REPO_URLS=https://github.com/me/repo-a=1,https://github.com/me/repo-b=4
# REPO_URL=https://github.com/me/repo-a
# RUNNER_REPLICAS=1

# --- Optional knobs (sensible defaults applied in docker-compose.yml) ----------

# Profile identity. The implicit default profile remains backward compatible.
RUNNER_PROFILE_ID=default

# The runner image each slot launches. The default base already ships PowerShell 7
# and a broad toolchain. To run the asserted variant instead, build it
# (`docker build -t self-hosted-runner:local .`) and set:
# RUNNER_IMAGE=self-hosted-runner:local
# Setup prepares the selected image before starting the manager, so generated
# profile state disables a second pull that could replace a verified mutable tag.
RUNNER_PULL_IMAGE=0

# Prefix for runner names in the GitHub UI (a slot/timestamp suffix is appended).
# RUNNER_NAME_PREFIX=runner

# Extra comma-separated labels. The default profile includes general-purpose.
# Isolated named profiles omit GitHub's default self-hosted/linux/architecture
# labels and receive explicit platform labels from the manager instead.
RUNNER_LABELS=general-purpose
RUNNER_NO_DEFAULT_LABELS=

# Optional organization/enterprise runner group.
# RUNNER_GROUP=

# --- Per-runner resource limits (optional; empty = unlimited) ------------------
# Without a cap, one heavy CI job (large .NET + coverage build, Vitest, Playwright)
# can exhaust host memory or fork unbounded processes. When the host runs out of
# memory the kernel OOM killer reaps runner processes fleet-wide at one instant —
# the "two runners lost communication at the same second" failure. Set these so a
# single job is throttled or OOM-killed in isolation instead of taking the host
# (and every sibling runner) down with it. Size them to the host: total across all
# concurrent slots should stay comfortably under physical RAM/cores.
#
# memory / memorySwap accept Docker byte values (e.g. 6g, 512m, 2147483648).
# Set RUNNER_MEMORY_SWAP_LIMIT equal to RUNNER_MEMORY_LIMIT to disable swap thrash.
# RUNNER_MEMORY_LIMIT=6g
# RUNNER_MEMORY_SWAP_LIMIT=6g
# cpus is a decimal core count (e.g. 4, 1.5).
# RUNNER_CPU_LIMIT=4
# pids is a positive integer process cap that contains fork bombs / orphans.
# RUNNER_PIDS_LIMIT=4096

# Profile-scoped directory mounted into the manager. Setup writes desired
# capacity atomically and the manager writes its accepted generation here.
PITCREW_STATE_DIR=.pitcrew-state/default
PITCREW_MANAGER_CONTRACT_VERSION=6